article.headline: South Florida 66, New Orleans 61
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- A trio of juniors combined for 35 points as South Florida rallied past New Orleans 66-61 Tuesday night to win the USF Holiday Classic for the fourth consecutive year. Guard Bradley Mosley led South Florida (6-5) with 14 points and took home the tournament's most-valuable player honors. Forward Terrence Leather added 11 points, and Brian Swift had 10 points and five assists. Kyle Buggs paced New Orleans (6-4) with 18 points. Johnell Smith scored 17, Bo McCalebb added 13. Swift scored seven of his points as the Bulls overcame a 56-42 deficit with a 18-1 run late in the second half. Buggs had a chance to pull the Privateers even at 64 with seven seconds left, but missed a 3-point shot from the left side. Smith, who joined Mosley in the all-tournament team backcourt, scored 10 points in the first half as the Privateers built a 27-15 lead. The Bulls responded with a 12-2 run to make it 29-27 at the break. South Florida is 25-5 all-time in the tournament.
